1
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:23,680
Alone again! On horseback again!

2
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,960
Though I don't think it's a sin to love to ride.

3
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:29,680
But I say, for example, it's time you had some restraint.

4
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:33,320
You're seventeen years old now!

5
00:02:33,640 --> 00:02:35,120
But still not 117!

6
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:37,120
Oh, uncle, don't lecture me!

7
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:40,080
How will you dress, Shurochka?

8
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:42,640
- You've decided to shine, haven't you? - It's no secret.

9
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:45,720
- I don't know, somehow... It's time to decide.

10
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:48,720
I'll still have time. The guests will not soon be in attendance.

11
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,320
The whole neighborhood is talking about the ball.

12
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:52,960
Ah, I have an idea!

13
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:58,000
I'll put on a costume to show you a fancy dress...

14
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,960
Hee-hee, you little brat!

15
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,200
Three thousand devils!

16
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:23,080
My dear!

17
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,040
Report that Brigadier Rzhevsky's nephew...

18
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:27,400
He has the honor to be with the Major's letter.

19
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:32,440
Well!!! Well, go on, why are you looking at me like a carrot?

20
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:47,640
I have an honor - Lieutenant Rzhevsky!

21
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,400
Are you a cornet?

22
00:03:49,482 --> 00:03:51,680
- Ah... Mmm... Your uniform is Pavlogradsky, of course!

23
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,600
- No!... I mean, yes! - What a surprise!

24
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:56,760
Please accept my brotherly salute to the cornet!

25
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,880
A hussar is a hussar's friend! Isn't it always true?

26
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:01,200
However, what brings you here?

27
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:04,560
Mmmm... Perhaps, by the will of providence, you're related to your masters?

28
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:06,720
- I... yes... - So much the better!

29
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:09,600
You will tell the truth about them now, without delay!

30
00:04:10,498 --> 00:04:13,159
- I am ready to serve! - Well, in short, here...

31
00:04:13,752 --> 00:04:16,589
The maiden Alexandra lives here, Like a certain Russian rose.

32
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:19,040
Ah, Shurochka! And she's my... cousin!

33
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:21,040
So fry everything you know about her.

34
00:04:21,738 --> 00:04:24,200
It's very important to me! Since my childhood days, I am, so to speak...

35
00:04:24,427 --> 00:04:27,910
I'm engaged to her in absentia. Have you heard, perhaps? If she's her cousin?

36
00:04:27,945 --> 00:04:30,160
That's right, I've heard of the affair.

37
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:33,840
- Is that you, then? - Alas, my friend.

38
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:36,794
- Why "alas"? - You're pontificating, of course.

39
00:04:37,172 --> 00:04:40,182
- Mmm.... I mean, yes! - You'll understand me then!

40
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,920
I'm a gambler, I'm a gambler, I'm a gambler, I'm a gambler.

41
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:45,920
But my uncle, an old fart, helped me out, On the condition...

42
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,197
...that I should marry now.

43
00:04:47,497 --> 00:04:49,705
I gave my word without looking, I was desperate...

44
00:04:49,966 --> 00:04:51,539
Or maybe I was drunk and out of my mind.

45
00:04:51,743 --> 00:04:53,695
But now, alas, there's my reckoning.

46
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:56,791
- I sympathize with you. - But is she rich?

47
00:04:57,009 --> 00:04:58,839
- Tell me? - Not at all.

48
00:04:59,101 --> 00:05:02,440
But I don't care if I sink in the sand or in the rocks.

49
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:04,640
- And if, for instance... What say you, cornet?

50
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:06,760
If your cousin does not like you, Lieutenant?

51
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,880
You are a green cornet. Hussars are not green...

52
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:11,800
They know not the word "no" in love.

53
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:14,080
And if I dare enter the gates of hell...

54
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:17,200
Any woman would be glad to be my friend.

55
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:22,762
But I want to know what she is, your cousin. Is she not pretty?

56
00:05:23,168 --> 00:05:24,454
- Oh, no! - Pretty?

57
00:05:24,713 --> 00:05:27,745
- I know not what to say. - Not so, not so. That's what I expected.

58
00:05:28,014 --> 00:05:30,302
She's what they call in the world, a prude...

59
00:05:30,470 --> 00:05:32,584
The word "ideal" never leaves her lips.

60
00:05:32,864 --> 00:05:36,714
She's fidgety and bawdy and silly, But she can grind rye with her tongue.

61
00:05:37,198 --> 00:05:40,827
- You, however, judge very wickedly. - Cornet, I am older than you.

62
00:05:41,003 --> 00:05:42,495
I know women better.

63
00:05:42,806 --> 00:05:44,843
You must have had too much luck with them.

64
00:05:45,123 --> 00:05:48,108
If I had wanted, I would have had occasion to marry a hundred times...

65
00:05:48,290 --> 00:05:50,317
But I've kept my freedom!

66
00:05:50,585 --> 00:05:53,164
- Are you as careful in battle? - CORNET!!!

67
00:05:53,808 --> 00:05:56,574
I did not mean to offend you, Lieutenant. Forgive me...

68
00:05:56,823 --> 00:05:58,784
Tell me, tell me in honor...

69
00:06:00,087 --> 00:06:03,553
Have you no amorous business with my wife?

70
00:06:03,771 --> 00:06:08,471
- I hope... I swear, Lieutenant, I have not yet shaved...

71
00:06:08,681 --> 00:06:11,060
Where shall I go to steal the hearts of fair fairies?

72
00:06:11,383 --> 00:06:15,409
- You moustachioed love-mongers have your hands full! - From now on I'll bail you out!

73
00:06:15,710 --> 00:06:20,942
- I'm very glad to meet you. - And I am a cornet. A hussar is a brother to a hussar!

74
00:06:29,343 --> 00:06:31,265
Lieutenant Rzhevsky.

75
00:06:33,716 --> 00:06:35,419
Here you are, at last, my light.

76
00:06:39,937 --> 00:06:41,584
- Have you seen your niece? - No, I haven't.

77
00:07:08,422 --> 00:07:09,912
I haven't seen you in a long time.

78
00:07:10,690 --> 00:07:12,681
Yes, there's a ball in our house.

79
00:07:13,356 --> 00:07:15,874
The bride is on her seventeenth birthday.

80
00:07:18,371 --> 00:07:22,675
You are asked to order in the kitchen For the sauce - what kind of broth?

81
00:07:23,038 --> 00:07:26,258
- Lieutenant Rzhevsky. - That's him.

82
00:07:43,869 --> 00:07:47,215
- I'm glad. - I'm happy... very me...

83
00:07:47,293 --> 00:07:51,385
In my own way, forgive me. Keep each other busy.

84
00:08:01,876 --> 00:08:05,588
Are you now coming to us from St. Petersburg or Moscow?

85
00:08:06,343 --> 00:08:08,237
My voyage is from Moscow.

86
00:08:08,824 --> 00:08:11,366
How do you like our quiet city?

87
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:15,852
You live in it, that's enough to make you like it.

88
00:08:16,365 --> 00:08:17,927
You are too kind.

89
00:08:18,125 --> 00:08:20,408
Hussars are used to speak plainly.

90
00:08:21,728 --> 00:08:23,573
What book do you like?

91
00:08:23,895 --> 00:08:25,607
For example, Quarissa.

92
00:08:26,140 --> 00:08:28,680
The other novels are no match, are they?

93
00:08:29,862 --> 00:08:33,272
How? I'm sorry, I haven't read it.

94
00:08:34,786 --> 00:08:36,379
Will you be with us long?

95
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:39,734
I've got a month's leave from the regiment.

96
00:08:39,984 --> 00:08:41,202
Yes, a month is running out.

97
00:08:46,008 --> 00:08:49,111
What kind of silks would you prefer for this drawing?

98
00:08:49,813 --> 00:08:52,916
Renge and Bordeaux are in fashion these days.

99
00:08:53,376 --> 00:08:58,122
I dare not advise you. Blue is the prettier of the two.

100
00:08:58,966 --> 00:09:04,247
Not you! Not you! Blue is out of tune, Bordeaux here, and gray thereafter.

101
00:09:04,356 --> 00:09:06,727
- Well, as you like. - Thank you.

102
00:09:06,996 --> 00:09:09,907
Would you like me to give you a pillow? When it's ready.

103
00:09:10,113 --> 00:09:12,985
No, I'm not worthy of such a favor.

104
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:17,013
I embroidered it with my own hand. Although, alas, it's not a new one.

105
00:09:21,713 --> 00:09:23,612
Let me ask you another question.

106
00:09:24,380 --> 00:09:26,316
- Do you like to cry? - Do I? Ha!

107
00:09:29,165 --> 00:09:31,834
There's nothing in the world sweeter than pure tears.

108
00:09:32,823 --> 00:09:37,572
- Have you read Werther? - No. I haven't read that one either.

109
00:09:38,349 --> 00:09:42,383
- You must read it, Charmaine. - Where is your uncle?

110
00:09:43,476 --> 00:09:46,368
Perhaps you have dreamed with the subject of your heart...

111
00:09:46,658 --> 00:09:48,231
...to sit by the sad moon?

112
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:51,509
And shed tears in perfect sorrow?

113
00:09:52,288 --> 00:09:55,387
If you have dreamed, I'll tell you a secret.

114
00:09:57,114 --> 00:09:59,682
Sir, the gentleman asks you to his office.

115
00:10:34,352 --> 00:10:36,106
Count Nourin!

116
00:10:37,086 --> 00:10:41,103
Count, we weren't expecting you at all, Such a surprise at our ball.

117
00:10:41,363 --> 00:10:43,740
Such an honor. You know each other?

118
00:10:44,692 --> 00:10:46,048
My niece.

119
00:10:46,253 --> 00:10:51,781
О! Alas. You must have been a child when I left your land.

120
00:10:51,997 --> 00:10:53,745
I wouldn't be surprised if you'd forgotten.

121
00:10:54,057 --> 00:10:57,210
- Well, what of Paris? - Oh, it's paradise

122
00:10:58,175 --> 00:11:01,603
Tell me, is it true that this autumn the French will be at war with us?

123
00:11:02,728 --> 00:11:06,768
Cédreux... There will be no war at all! I think, though I am no coward...

124
00:11:06,792 --> 00:11:12,896
We can't compete with Europe. Is it possible?! La France and us?

125
00:11:13,218 --> 00:11:16,520
No, the best minds in the world would not advise us to fight.

126
00:11:44,916 --> 00:11:47,173
I left you the last cotillion.

127
00:11:47,378 --> 00:11:48,530
I'm happy!

128
00:11:49,157 --> 00:11:52,727
Between the figures let's end our conversation about perfect tears.

129
00:11:53,019 --> 00:11:57,336
I wish I could persuade you, if you don't agree.

130
00:11:57,707 --> 00:12:00,323
There's half a chapter like that in Wurtar...!

131
00:12:00,561 --> 00:12:01,627
- Ah... - Mm-mm!!!

132
00:12:10,524 --> 00:12:13,909
Oh, Shurochka, sing us a verse, What the Lieutenant sang last time.

133
00:12:14,071 --> 00:12:15,679
- At the governor's. - Now?

134
00:12:15,906 --> 00:12:17,450
- Oh, yes. - That's what we're all asking.

135
00:12:28,099 --> 00:12:31,662
/Singing/: Young Pretty Woman, I bid you farewell.

136
00:12:31,952 --> 00:12:35,375
Let a bullet of good fortune cut my way on earth.

137
00:12:35,677 --> 00:12:39,248
If I should fall, in unequal battle...

138
00:12:39,561 --> 00:12:43,457
...but, Armida, remember, remember my short life.

139
00:12:44,181 --> 00:12:47,798
In the bloody saddle my horse bears me.

140
00:12:48,141 --> 00:12:51,774
To the tender green maples From a strange fire.

141
00:12:52,398 --> 00:12:55,701
"My hussar's tunic is on fire, Opened from the shoulder...

142
00:12:56,066 --> 00:12:59,671
...In crimson yellow light, the light of the last ray.

143
00:13:00,276 --> 00:13:04,593
The sunset with its invisible hand Blesses me.

144
00:13:04,951 --> 00:13:08,979
And the memorial willow tree rustles softly...

145
00:13:09,302 --> 00:13:12,849
...There is no higher place in the world To dream, to love and to sing.

146
00:13:13,223 --> 00:13:17,144
And in my native land, in my native land, to fight and die.

147
00:13:19,844 --> 00:13:21,410
- Lovely! - Cut. Sharman.

148
00:13:22,747 --> 00:13:24,750
You should be an actor, Shura.

149
00:13:24,928 --> 00:13:26,580
Their whole life is an affair.

150
00:13:26,797 --> 00:13:28,060
No, it's not my nature.

151
00:13:28,150 --> 00:13:30,309
I'll be back in my masquerade costume.

152
00:13:32,347 --> 00:13:33,322
Mazurka. Madame Angéozhe!

153
00:13:55,375 --> 00:13:57,587
Well, finally, cornet, where have you disappeared to?

154
00:13:58,200 --> 00:14:00,984
I've been looking for you everywhere. It's so boring here.

155
00:14:01,264 --> 00:14:04,325
I'm at your service, sir, all the way. But is it possible to be bored at a ball?

156
00:14:04,625 --> 00:14:07,898
I'll have to reproach my cousin, for she's kept you badly occupied.

157
00:14:08,106 --> 00:14:12,220
I have taken much from her. I'll never forget this day.

158
00:14:12,799 --> 00:14:14,383
By the way, you spoke to her, didn't you?

159
00:14:14,557 --> 00:14:16,353
- Who? - My cousin, damn it.

160
00:14:16,509 --> 00:14:18,694
When I think of her, I feel sick in the back of my head.

161
00:14:18,994 --> 00:14:21,134
Yeah! You played the snake, didn't you?

162
00:14:21,371 --> 00:14:24,198
...and I got all her impressions of the groom candidate.

163
00:14:24,509 --> 00:14:26,617
И? She's in love with him, isn't she?

164
00:14:27,113 --> 00:14:29,374
She's all "ha-ha" and "hee-hee" and "hee-hee-hee.

165
00:14:30,202 --> 00:14:32,697
No, she didn't like you terribly.

166
00:14:33,255 --> 00:14:34,649
What do you mean, she didn't like you?

167
00:14:35,004 --> 00:14:37,542
She said you complimented her in vain.

168
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:38,931
I did?

169
00:14:39,121 --> 00:14:42,503
She said she had never met a cheekier man.

170
00:14:42,846 --> 00:14:46,513
I beg your pardon, you've got a moustache hanging like a bastard...

171
00:14:46,834 --> 00:14:50,242
What?! You're as bold as she is! I am!... I am!!!

172
00:14:50,502 --> 00:14:52,663
That from manners one can see the habit of horses.

173
00:14:52,942 --> 00:14:56,308
I will not give one mare for a hundred such maidens!!!

174
00:14:56,618 --> 00:15:01,900
That of all the familiar faces she hath not seen, pardon me, a nastier snout.

175
00:15:02,288 --> 00:15:05,803
Aye? A thousand devils! Maybe it's for the best.

176
00:15:06,086 --> 00:15:08,322
If you don't like him, you can't marry him.

177
00:15:08,603 --> 00:15:10,879
Not a bit. She also said...

178
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,408
...that it is no longer for her to change my uncle's will.

179
00:15:13,697 --> 00:15:16,158
That if he commanded it, she would go for the beast.

180
00:15:16,503 --> 00:15:17,728
That she can even train bears.

181
00:15:17,934 --> 00:15:20,325
Enough! I trust you now as a brother.

182
00:15:20,838 --> 00:15:22,953
You are my first friend among all men.

183
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:25,591
Well, you're a wiggler! Fool! Sour girl.

184
00:15:25,850 --> 00:15:27,171
So, you've decided not to get married?

185
00:15:27,418 --> 00:15:29,607
I wish I could. But I gave my word to my uncle.

186
00:15:29,878 --> 00:15:31,917
I owe him a debt. And with this I pay my debt.

187
00:15:32,261 --> 00:15:34,386
Don't be discouraged at the masquerade! Come, let us dance.

188
00:15:34,625 --> 00:15:37,454
No. I will have a drink with you on the brotherhood.

189
00:15:37,657 --> 00:15:39,051
There's a lovely cliquot here.

190
00:15:39,609 --> 00:15:41,639
Your offer is too flattering.

191
00:15:42,184 --> 00:15:44,609
- But we are of different ranks. - For pity's sake, what nonsense!

192
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:48,563
Know that wherever a hussar's spurs ring, there's equality.

193
00:16:15,185 --> 00:16:17,301
Attention, gentlemen, I ask for everyone's attention.

194
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:19,815
Trouble has come upon our homeland.

195
00:16:20,417 --> 00:16:22,740
A storm of war has covered our skies.

196
00:16:23,201 --> 00:16:27,313
On the thirteenth day, Bonaparte's armies have crossed the Neman.

197
00:16:29,093 --> 00:16:30,425
The moment of trial is at hand.

198
00:16:30,971 --> 00:16:33,324
I hope all of you will faithfully do your duty.

199
00:16:33,853 --> 00:16:36,508
All officers, please return to the regiment.

200
00:16:37,429 --> 00:16:38,407
Very well!

201
00:16:38,794 --> 00:16:40,629
We'll meet the hour with dignity.

202
00:16:41,055 --> 00:16:42,894
I beg you, ball, now I'll stop.

203
00:16:43,299 --> 00:16:45,863
- Forgive me, my friend. - Ah, your lordship, what are you.

204
00:16:45,951 --> 00:16:50,039
You're ready to die for your country. There's no happier part under the moon...

205
00:16:50,287 --> 00:16:52,420
Than to die for my country! Isn't that so, Cornet?

206
00:17:04,611 --> 00:17:07,388
- I'll take my leave. - I know it's not my destiny.

207
00:17:10,650 --> 00:17:12,370
Write, my friend.

208
00:17:14,657 --> 00:17:16,726
With you, cornet, we'll find each other.

209
00:17:16,985 --> 00:17:20,370
If we shall not be killed in the war, When our victories shine...

210
00:17:20,620 --> 00:17:23,163
Will you not bid farewell to your cousin? Shall I call?

211
00:17:23,401 --> 00:17:25,645
I will not. I am not worthy of this maiden.

212
00:17:26,207 --> 00:17:30,041
Tell her I bow. Let me kiss thee, in love.

213
00:18:04,932 --> 00:18:06,170
Ah, Shurochka.

214
00:18:07,558 --> 00:18:11,414
Pardon me, the costume is excellent, bravo. And in the spirit of the day.

215
00:18:11,598 --> 00:18:12,885
Lovely, isn't it?

216
00:18:14,311 --> 00:18:16,849
We've been talking amongst ourselves, How we can help the troops.

217
00:18:17,065 --> 00:18:18,785
We've decided to make a corpse out of rags...

218
00:18:18,970 --> 00:18:20,712
- For the infirmary. - Tomorrow at five.

219
00:18:48,414 --> 00:18:57,940
*What did he say? ♪ There's no greater battle for my country under the moon ♪

220
00:19:00,109 --> 00:19:03,935
*♪ If it were up to me, I'd want to die ♪

221
00:19:03,959 --> 00:19:07,889
To die in battle. On a war horse, flying like the wind.

222
00:19:12,326 --> 00:19:18,583
Oh, young lady, what wonders in the world, a hussar. And the posture's perfect.

223
00:19:19,376 --> 00:19:25,894
I wish you had a horse. And a foam on your muzzle. And a sabre, and you'd be on parade.

224
00:19:26,134 --> 00:19:33,459
I'd be glad to serve as such a young man again, though I've served much.

225
00:19:37,110 --> 00:19:39,669
Go to bed. They've all gone from the ball.

226
00:19:45,782 --> 00:19:50,142
Tell me, would you serve with me again, if I were a man?

227
00:19:52,743 --> 00:19:59,488
I begged the master to let me go, if I had reason to be choked, that the enemy was coming to my country.

228
00:20:00,027 --> 00:20:04,188
I'd like to be in battle once more. To shed blood for my people.

229
00:20:04,530 --> 00:20:07,466
Take me with you! I do not laugh!

230
00:20:07,653 --> 00:20:10,542
A hussar before you! I know how to shoot, you taught me!

231
00:20:10,963 --> 00:20:14,571
You just said I should have a horse. I've made up my mind, there's no more way for me!

232
00:20:14,595 --> 00:20:19,401
Are you jesting with an old man? I'll tell the lord to look after you.

233
00:20:19,766 --> 00:20:23,817
You can't stop me with words. If you forbid me, I'll run away all the same.

234
00:20:24,192 --> 00:20:26,801
There's only one thing on Russians' minds now: How to save my homeland.

235
00:20:27,132 --> 00:20:29,215
And I'm here with needlework and dolls.

236
00:20:29,526 --> 00:20:32,997
No, I want to try what I'm worth. And in battle!

237
00:20:33,322 --> 00:20:37,927
And if I'm killed, blame yourself for my death. I didn't want to be my orderly.

238
00:20:38,227 --> 00:20:42,001
To fight with me in the war! Well, farewell!

239
00:20:42,896 --> 00:20:46,054
You'll be recognized!

240
00:20:46,473 --> 00:20:51,109
Fear not, old man, no one will know. So I must go away alone?

241
00:20:52,350 --> 00:20:55,664
God owns the brave. What about my uncle?

242
00:20:56,079 --> 00:20:58,897
He'll go mad if he doesn't find you at the manor in the morning.

243
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:01,438
A maiden to the camp. And he's all about the wedding.

244
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:03,303
I'll write to him from the road.

245
00:21:05,340 --> 00:21:06,634
Well, what are you sitting there?

246
00:21:07,191 --> 00:21:10,325
Tell him to lock the doors. I'll go out the window.

247
00:21:13,707 --> 00:21:17,741
Forgive me, according to the Christian faith, If I am foolishly guilty.

248
00:21:21,749 --> 00:21:23,960
I'm ready to serve as a Suvorov soldier.

249
00:21:25,493 --> 00:21:28,801
We'll leave now. I'll wait here for you.

250
00:21:29,437 --> 00:21:32,476
- Saddle your horse. - I'll not deceive you.

251
00:21:40,547 --> 00:21:44,993
# Farewell to my old home, perhaps forever #

252
00:21:47,242 --> 00:21:49,433
