256
00:22:33,827 --> 00:22:46,169
/ Sings a lyrical song:/ Moonlit meadows, The night is as bright as day.

257
00:22:48,421 --> 00:23:01,077
Sleep, my Svetlana, Sleep as I slept.

258
00:23:03,439 --> 00:23:16,249
# In the corner of the pillow, tuck your nose in... #

259
00:23:18,181 --> 00:23:30,598
The stars, like freckles, Shine down peacefully.

260
00:23:32,986 --> 00:23:45,574
The moonlit garden rustles quietly in its leaves.

261
00:23:47,918 --> 00:24:00,215
The day is coming, What does it promise?

262
00:24:02,267 --> 00:24:14,592
The candle burns out, It burns to the ground.

263
00:24:16,456 --> 00:24:30,949
Sleep, my heart, Sleep as I slept.

264
00:24:54,381 --> 00:24:55,745
I hear the noise of battle.

265
00:24:56,257 --> 00:25:00,669
Yes, the army is near. What do you say? Where are you from and who are you?

266
00:25:01,185 --> 00:25:03,892
I'll say I'm behind the regiment. That I want to fight

267
00:25:03,916 --> 00:25:06,484
I want to fight again. No one will reproach me for lying.

268
00:25:07,139 --> 00:25:08,986
Oh, young lady. Do you see there in the rye?

269
00:25:19,693 --> 00:25:21,160
What's the matter with you, Captain?

270
00:25:25,173 --> 00:25:26,706
I have a bullet in my chest.

271
00:25:27,393 --> 00:25:30,462
I have with me a packet of the most important report.

272
00:25:31,286 --> 00:25:35,943
Cornet, I beseech you to finish the task given me by the field-marshal.

273
00:25:36,757 --> 00:25:43,692
and set forth at once. Across the river, our rearguard is fighting Murat.

274
00:25:44,269 --> 00:25:45,796
I'll prove myself trustworthy.

275
00:25:45,960 --> 00:25:49,566
Come, cornet. Ride, God be with you.

276
00:25:52,103 --> 00:25:54,615
He is badly wounded. Stay with him, Ivan.

277
00:25:54,950 --> 00:25:55,768
But, young lady...

278
00:25:57,768 --> 00:26:00,937
Look. See you, Captain!

279
00:27:55,700 --> 00:27:58,581
A package for you, your lordship, from the field marshal.

280
00:27:58,617 --> 00:28:00,468
What, blood? Are you not wounded, Cornet?

281
00:28:00,711 --> 00:28:03,289
It is the messenger's blood. He gave me this packet.

282
00:28:03,313 --> 00:28:06,042
The packet was on his breast, but the bullet pierced his chest.

283
00:28:06,283 --> 00:28:10,877
My friend, we are, unfortunately, at war. And you are a cornet, a cavalryman of talent.

284
00:28:11,082 --> 00:28:14,552
I would gladly take you on. Will you be my junior adjutant at headquarters?

285
00:28:14,705 --> 00:28:15,653
I'm glad.

