00:31:04,436 --> 00:31:06,788
I came from headquarters with the relay.

310
00:31:07,923 --> 00:31:10,868
Oh, you came? Who do you want?

311
00:31:10,892 --> 00:31:12,031
I'm the adjutant.

312
00:31:12,449 --> 00:31:13,734
I can see it in your eyes that you're an adjutant.

313
00:31:13,911 --> 00:31:16,334
- Who shall I hand this package to? Vasilyev on reconnaissance.

314
00:31:16,358 --> 00:31:19,033
And the assistant? Who can I give this order to?

315
00:31:19,293 --> 00:31:22,985
About the assistant, it's easier than that. Lieutenant! To you!

316
00:31:23,157 --> 00:31:25,913
And I'll ask you to stand in front of the headquarters!

317
00:31:26,149 --> 00:31:27,650
/Great laughter/

318
00:31:28,241 --> 00:31:31,528
HQ again? You'd better send some vodka.

319
00:31:33,926 --> 00:31:38,813
What a meeting! Is that you? Lieutenant...

320
00:31:39,007 --> 00:31:43,184
Where are you from, brother, and what's your fate? I didn't think I'd meet you here.

321
00:31:43,495 --> 00:31:46,887
I didn't recognize you at once. But you have come at a good hour.

322
00:31:47,094 --> 00:31:47,952
They know each other!

323
00:31:48,042 --> 00:31:49,924
I brought you orders from the corps headquarters.

324
00:31:50,165 --> 00:31:54,290
I don't give a damn about orders. Gentlemen! Cornet Azarov! My old friend.

325
00:31:54,470 --> 00:31:56,421
Love and respect to the Hussar!

326
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:57,501
We are glad to see you!

327
00:31:57,525 --> 00:32:00,061
We're always happy to invite you to our tight bivouac circle.

328
00:32:00,309 --> 00:32:02,349
- The hospitality of the partisans is well known. - Is the porridge ready?

329
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:06,040
We ask you to share our breakfast with your new friends.

330
00:32:06,256 --> 00:32:07,867
By any chance did you bring a bottle with you?

331
00:32:08,013 --> 00:32:10,963
No. I guess you haven't had much experience as an officer.

332
00:32:13,870 --> 00:32:16,294
So, tell me about yourself, Cornet. How are you doing?

333
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:18,207
Quite happy with my service.

334
00:32:19,233 --> 00:32:23,288
Yes, my cousin asked me to say hello if I meet you.

335
00:32:23,545 --> 00:32:25,925
Well, I beg your friendship, don't think of her.

336
00:32:26,127 --> 00:32:30,434
- Who's that cousin? - I've got Rzhevsky. - Here's your answer.

337
00:32:30,808 --> 00:32:33,478
It's embarrassing to think of that meeting.

338
00:32:33,873 --> 00:32:35,661
Hey, you white-haired bastard.

339
00:32:35,921 --> 00:32:39,162
- It's nothing, really. - We know those tricks.

340
00:32:39,186 --> 00:32:42,833
All right, I'll tell you! He's the witness.

341
00:32:44,985 --> 00:32:48,165
My uncle, the foreman, has decided to marry me.

342
00:32:49,557 --> 00:32:54,947
That's the sorriest day I've ever known. The bride, my God... I'm in a cold sweat.

343
00:32:55,013 --> 00:32:56,388
Is she so ugly?

344
00:32:56,732 --> 00:33:00,481
It's true to say, I think she's a freak of note.

345
00:33:01,748 --> 00:33:05,820
- What are you, cornet? - No, you're not fair! She's pretty!

346
00:33:06,193 --> 00:33:11,242
What are you saying? Her nose is like a plum, her eyes are like a plum, her braids are like bunting.

347
00:33:11,276 --> 00:33:12,256
What a scarecrow.

348
00:33:12,405 --> 00:33:16,766
She's a fool! Isn't she? But she's not ugly! I'll vouch for that.

349
00:33:16,974 --> 00:33:21,494
Our tastes are different, then. In your way, but in general it's disgusting.

350
00:33:21,603 --> 00:33:26,899
And what's most unpleasant, you may imagine, is that she fell in love with me at once.

351
00:33:28,768 --> 00:33:31,198
- What are you cornet? - No, nothing!

352
00:33:31,768 --> 00:33:38,363
There was a ball in the evening! She wandered after me like a shadow everywhere. She never took her eyes off me.

353
00:33:38,768 --> 00:33:41,235
Admit it, Rzhevsky, you didn't tell us everything.

354
00:33:41,304 --> 00:33:45,287
I suppose you kissed her in a ballroom whirl, In some secluded corner...

355
00:33:45,919 --> 00:33:49,243
I, gentlemen, am afraid to be immodest, but I have kissed...

356
00:33:49,933 --> 00:33:52,071
- What's the matter, cornet? - Nay, nothing.

357
00:33:52,303 --> 00:33:54,516
There's no great sin in it, and I could not rightly

358
00:33:54,540 --> 00:33:57,132
when she was about to tear herself from her dress!

359
00:34:01,101 --> 00:34:02,815
Well, good fellow, eh?

360
00:34:03,031 --> 00:34:06,244
I hate with a passion the priggish, sour, sour woman.

361
00:34:06,429 --> 00:34:08,694
If such a one were in trouble, I'd not lift a hand

362
00:34:08,718 --> 00:34:10,701
I would not lift a hand to avert the danger.

363
00:34:10,757 --> 00:34:14,853
What if my cousin were in trouble? Would you not feel pity for her?

364
00:34:15,122 --> 00:34:18,341
- Certainly not! - I'll wager you! I'll wager you!

365
00:34:18,527 --> 00:34:20,288
- You! - You! You slander for nothing!

366
00:34:20,491 --> 00:34:24,173
I'll wager with you that if the occasion should come...

367
00:34:24,656 --> 00:34:27,286
That I'll save a fashionable woman with my own hand, I'll...

368
00:34:27,566 --> 00:34:28,815
You must marry her!

369
00:34:29,020 --> 00:34:31,010
Damn it, that'll never happen!

370
00:34:31,163 --> 00:34:33,038
I'll ask our hands to separate!

371
00:34:34,926 --> 00:34:37,768
There's a French wagon train crawling through the woods!

372
00:34:38,225 --> 00:34:41,179
Follow me, my friends, we'll treat them to Russian!

373
00:36:43,375 --> 00:36:49,454
What's in here? Carpets and piles of silk. Weapons? That's a good one for us, by the way.

374
00:36:49,701 --> 00:36:56,057
There's more trophy there. Wow, hussars rejoice, wine!

375
00:36:56,254 --> 00:36:57,384
Cheers!

376
00:37:01,042 --> 00:37:07,517
Wait! If my eyes do not lie, Germont Louise! Gentlemen, am I dreaming or am I delirious?

377
00:37:08,110 --> 00:37:10,683
- This way, Germont! - From where?

378
00:37:10,719 --> 00:37:13,542
It's very nice, but you're not happy, I see.

379
00:37:13,791 --> 00:37:16,134
I would sooner believe in a bird that suddenly popped out of a brook, ...

380
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:21,181
Than in this, on the road, here, the goddess of dreams, the dream of fairies. And this is a dream.

381
00:37:21,355 --> 00:37:23,808
Flattery is nice to me. That's me.

382
00:37:24,650 --> 00:37:28,011
Quick, where's Lymov?! Come here! I know you, don't I?

383
00:37:28,906 --> 00:37:32,267
I was a slave to your beauty, wasn't I, last fall.

384
00:37:38,603 --> 00:37:41,325
But tell me more clearly, where are you from? At least the gist of it.

385
00:37:41,923 --> 00:37:45,089
You're spinning on pins and needles, Lieutenant. Let me breathe.

386
00:37:45,275 --> 00:37:48,269
But we will not let the French have you now. Won't we, brothers?

387
00:37:48,645 --> 00:37:51,165
My God. From now on, I have no desire to return to them myself.

388
00:37:51,342 --> 00:37:54,182
Hurrah for Germont! Hurray for Germont!

389
00:37:57,176 --> 00:38:03,905
/ Singing:/ When the punch of purple flames All around again, all around again illuminated.

390
00:38:04,104 --> 00:38:07,270
The chorus of the beloved shall be sung again.

391
00:38:07,294 --> 00:38:12,078
A long time ago, a long time ago, a long time ago!

392
00:38:12,644 --> 00:38:19,276
We're all a little superstitious, But we believe hard, we believe only in wine.

393
00:38:19,672 --> 00:38:22,851
In it we drown all our chimeras.

394
00:38:22,875 --> 00:38:27,680
A long time ago, a long time ago, a long time ago!

395
00:38:28,588 --> 00:38:35,087
The glory of the smoke hangs over us, And only, only one thing torments us.

396
00:38:35,806 --> 00:38:39,048
Hearts without practice rust.

397
00:38:39,072 --> 00:38:43,971
A long time ago, a long time ago, a long time ago!

398
00:38:44,698 --> 00:38:48,334
In battles, not in bed, To part

399
00:38:48,358 --> 00:38:51,252
with life, we are destined to part.

400
00:38:52,094 --> 00:38:56,427
The popes must have been singing us off.

401
00:38:56,451 --> 00:39:02,987
A long time ago, a long time ago, a long time ago!

402
00:39:04,825 --> 00:39:06,679
For the Motherland, Mother Russia!

403
00:39:06,949 --> 00:39:10,011
I, gentlemen, want to say, In many countries I have played,...

404
00:39:10,396 --> 00:39:14,065
But it's only here with you that I cherish my success. I love you all!

405
00:39:14,428 --> 00:39:16,207
Russia has become dear to me, too.

406
00:39:16,313 --> 00:39:20,096
- Yay, Germont! - Now it's your turn to sing.

407
00:39:20,356 --> 00:39:21,270
- Please! - Yes.

408
00:39:21,466 --> 00:39:23,921
No, you're right, gentlemen. I have forgotten everything.

409
00:39:24,221 --> 00:39:26,622
Your memory has always been bad.

410
00:39:26,761 --> 00:39:29,559
Oh no. I remembered one verse.

411
00:39:30,208 --> 00:39:34,287
But don't judge too harshly - War, excitement, the road.

412
00:39:39,027 --> 00:39:49,076
/ Sings: / Call me, my beloved. Forget all that was, my beloved.

413
00:39:49,539 --> 00:40:00,736
Let's forget what happened, my beloved. There is no power more miraculous than the power of love.

414
00:40:03,232 --> 00:40:10,833
Let the wine splash, I drink, it's not enough for me. I drink, I'm not enough, I'm drunk.

415
00:40:11,124 --> 00:40:17,119
