419
00:40:56,598 --> 00:41:05,174
I'm drinking, I'm drinking, I'm drinking, I'm drinking, I'm drinking, I'm drinking, I'm drunk.

420
00:41:05,656 --> 00:41:11,364
I drink all I can't get enough, I'm already drunk, And the hall is spinning, I drink all I can't get enough.

421
00:41:11,697 --> 00:41:26,006
I'm not drinking enough, I'm already drunk, And the hall is spinning, I don't care anymore!

422
00:41:26,499 --> 00:41:30,727
- Bravo! Bravo! - You are worthy to be a goddess!

423
00:41:30,900 --> 00:41:31,925
Don't lose your head, brother.

424
00:41:32,195 --> 00:41:35,359
And I have no pity for you, Louise, All is nothing before you!

425
00:41:35,779 --> 00:41:37,877
The fortune teller is destined to love the brown-haired girl.

426
00:41:38,113 --> 00:41:40,755
- You what? - No, nothing! Sit down, Cornet.

427
00:41:41,497 --> 00:41:45,632
Lymov, I'll tell you a secret, If you're a faithful friend.

428
00:41:45,817 --> 00:41:47,164
I love you more and more every hour.

429
00:41:47,677 --> 00:41:53,819
I don't like actresses! First of all. And secondly... I forgot. Pour it!

430
00:41:58,455 --> 00:42:03,793
Fortune-tellers always lie! For you, Lieutenant, I speak now!

431
00:42:03,955 --> 00:42:04,851
He's very nice.

432
00:42:05,141 --> 00:42:07,247
He's just a boy. No, give me your elbow.

433
00:42:07,355 --> 00:42:10,186
- It's too much. - You're not jealous?

434
00:42:10,933 --> 00:42:11,877
Oh, not at all.

435
00:42:12,023 --> 00:42:17,811
I've never drunk so much in my life I swear on my life, my life...

436
00:42:18,027 --> 00:42:22,115
...Was... Yes, I was! I'll sing!

437
00:42:22,289 --> 00:42:26,684
- You? Yes, now! Please be quiet!

438
00:42:26,886 --> 00:42:29,093
- We ask! - Just don't fake it.

439
00:42:29,161 --> 00:42:34,043
- He's so full of youth. - Mademoiselle, I was listening to you.

440
00:42:41,166 --> 00:42:48,442
/ Singing in a drunken voice:/ They call me a youth without youth. I don't care, I don't care, I don't care!

441
00:42:49,021 --> 00:42:51,769
At least they don't call me a coward!

442
00:42:51,793 --> 00:42:56,591
A long time ago, a long time ago, a long time ago!

443
00:42:57,762 --> 00:43:04,014
Otherwise he twirls his whiskers furiously, Bottles to all, bottles to all, looks at the bottom of them all.

444
00:43:04,819 --> 00:43:07,523
But he himself is only a copy of the Hussar.

445
00:43:07,547 --> 00:43:12,093
A long time ago, a long time ago, a long time ago!

446
00:43:12,829 --> 00:43:19,384
And some swear by passion, But when the wine has been drunk, when the wine has been drunk...

447
00:43:20,224 --> 00:43:24,193
...All his passion is at the bottom of the bottle.

448
00:43:24,217 --> 00:43:29,236
A long time ago, a long time ago, a long time ago!

449
00:43:30,084 --> 00:43:36,411
The sea is knee-deep in lovers. I am with them in this, with them in this.

450
00:43:36,961 --> 00:43:40,515
But treason is waiting for everyone.

451
00:43:40,539 --> 00:43:46,731
A long time ago, a long time ago, a long time ago!

452
00:43:47,870 --> 00:43:49,489
- What's wrong with him? - It's not good.

453
00:43:49,822 --> 00:43:51,457
- Azarov! - Water!

454
00:43:51,589 --> 00:43:54,501
We old hobos don't care about this feast now, do we?

455
00:43:54,627 --> 00:43:55,511
Now, unbutton that uniform.

456
00:43:55,750 --> 00:44:01,107
No, no!!! Я.. I'm a little hot.

457
00:44:01,131 --> 00:44:02,131
I don't like women, though.

458
00:44:05,383 --> 00:44:08,213
I don't like women, though.

459
00:44:11,262 --> 00:44:12,718
How your eyes shine brightly.

460
00:44:12,742 --> 00:44:14,304
- Lieutenant! - Just a kiss, please.

461
00:44:14,457 --> 00:44:15,260
No, no.

462
00:44:15,407 --> 00:44:19,788
Deserve what? Idea! I'll be right back.

463
00:44:27,872 --> 00:44:31,641
Pierre. Do you really not even want to say a word to me?

464
00:44:32,177 --> 00:44:32,791
Believe me...

465
00:44:32,815 --> 00:44:34,729
There's no need to go on, everything is clear without words.

466
00:44:34,890 --> 00:44:36,213
My friend, do you want the truth?

467
00:44:36,419 --> 00:44:40,046
No, I'm not playing this game anymore, I don't want truth or lies.

468
00:44:40,254 --> 00:44:41,426
But, Pierre, please.

469
00:44:41,643 --> 00:44:44,408
I ask you as much, in my life do not confuse me.

470
00:44:44,646 --> 00:44:47,808
- You will be sorry. - Maybe. But even then I won't change.

471
00:44:48,142 --> 00:44:52,777
- Pierre, I have been faithful to you, I swear. - Let's keep our vows, too.

472
00:44:55,425 --> 00:44:59,187
- Here's my surprise! - Flowers? Where did you get them?

473
00:44:59,394 --> 00:45:04,182
In the midst of winter such a miracle? Lieutenant! I promised you nothing.

474
00:45:04,300 --> 00:45:05,337
Have mercy!

475
00:45:05,520 --> 00:45:09,230
I want to give the flowers to the one who is the dearest of you all.

476
00:45:09,720 --> 00:45:13,165
- It's a custom in Provence. - My flowers? But why?

477
00:45:13,295 --> 00:45:14,871
And she will give it to Lymov.

478
00:45:15,110 --> 00:45:20,840
Pour me some more wine. Cornet, I drink a glass to you!

479
00:45:21,288 --> 00:45:23,754
Give me the flower now. Give it to me now!

480
00:45:23,884 --> 00:45:26,175
At least you'll concede. A hop hit him in the head.

481
00:45:26,368 --> 00:45:29,755
- He is devilishly hot in resentment. - Thank you, mademoiselle!

482
00:45:30,582 --> 00:45:37,812
All right! Please come to the barrier. I challenge you! Yes, yes!

483
00:45:38,291 --> 00:45:43,640
Are you silent? The rank of officer, you coward, is not worthy then.

484
00:45:45,841 --> 00:45:49,375
I ask to be my second. Pierre Lymov, you as well as you!

485
00:45:49,538 --> 00:45:51,536
But he is on duty as an adjutant to leave us tomorrow.

486
00:45:51,721 --> 00:45:53,119
Immediately we will fight!

487
00:45:53,289 --> 00:45:54,426
- But where? - Over there!

488
00:45:54,608 --> 00:45:57,127
- However, brothers, how is it possible? - Here, now, a duel?

489
00:45:57,386 --> 00:45:59,012
- Please... No, mademoiselle!

490
00:45:59,196 --> 00:46:00,112
To the barrier!

491
00:46:00,136 --> 00:46:02,957
God... Atonement, I will kiss you myself.

492
00:46:04,648 --> 00:46:12,722
Shit... I'm losing my mind. I am willing to forgive the insult.

493
00:46:12,863 --> 00:46:15,655
But I don't need your condescension!

494
00:46:15,914 --> 00:46:18,634
- What a mess. - Told you I was sorry.

495
00:46:18,724 --> 00:46:23,541
No! If you're not willing to shoot You must ask my forgiveness!

496
00:46:23,565 --> 00:46:27,627
In Russia there will never be this compote, That I ask for forgiveness!

497
00:46:28,065 --> 00:46:31,053
Yes! Shoot here and now!

498
00:46:42,120 --> 00:46:46,182
Another warning. Will you friends make peace after all?

499
00:46:46,335 --> 00:46:49,159
- Oh, you shouldn't have. - I have been insulted here.

500
00:47:00,096 --> 00:47:04,126
Get together! I count. One.

501
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:10,619
Two.

502
00:47:14,750 --> 00:47:15,495
Three.

503
00:47:16,652 --> 00:47:18,312
- Davyd! - Colonel!

504
00:47:20,134 --> 00:47:22,629
- What's going on here? - A duel with this dandy.

505
00:47:22,885 --> 00:47:27,071
How dare you, in time of military action? In the hour of our fatherland's distress.

506
00:47:27,594 --> 00:47:30,730
Is not occasion enough for another firing? Stand down!

507
00:47:31,157 --> 00:47:35,831
If I hear again of this scandalous cause, I'll punish you with a fitting punishment.

508
00:47:35,929 --> 00:47:40,032
I'll punish him without regard to valor or rank. Where did this cornet come from?

509
00:47:40,270 --> 00:47:42,207
I have brought you a packet from corps headquarters.

510
00:47:42,899 --> 00:47:46,697
You, cornet, have you no other amusement here than to duel?

511
00:47:48,718 --> 00:47:52,431
Bah. What do I see? Are you, mademoiselle? Where did you come from?

512
00:47:52,455 --> 00:47:55,671
Where the devil did you come from? Am I dreaming?

513
00:47:55,880 --> 00:47:58,473
- No, it's me. - It's the wonder of wonders!

514
00:47:58,844 --> 00:48:01,851
Sheherazade in the midst of my hangers-on.

515
00:48:06,895 --> 00:48:10,601
Friends, the field marshal thanks us!

516
00:48:10,768 --> 00:48:11,787
- Himself? - Yes!

517
00:48:12,513 --> 00:48:15,380
- Here's the signature, "N. Kutuzov"! -Oh, really?

518
00:48:15,558 --> 00:48:16,470
Let me see!

519
00:48:17,334 --> 00:48:20,694
If we all beat the French like you, the enemy would be defeated!

520
00:48:21,217 --> 00:48:24,238
It's the partisans' habit to fight without fear of death.

521
00:48:24,751 --> 00:48:29,622
- We beat our enemies wherever we meet them! - Long time ago, long time ago!

522
00:48:30,061 --> 00:48:35,686
Colonel! I beg you. Can't you find a place in the detachment for a cornet?

523
00:48:35,916 --> 00:48:37,363
- I mean, for you? - Yes.

524
00:48:37,633 --> 00:48:41,078
No, my friend, alas. A cornet in a detachment is a bad omen.

525
00:51:48,856 --> 00:51:51,017
Thank you, my brave savior.

526
00:51:51,764 --> 00:51:53,871
Accept my heartfelt gratitude.

527
00:51:55,945 --> 00:51:57,104
But how did you do it?

528
00:51:57,128 --> 00:52:00,850
It all worked out, didn't it? Here at headquarters, you'll find everything you need.

529
00:52:01,404 --> 00:52:03,946
I must go. Excuse me, service.

530
00:52:04,048 --> 00:52:06,331
I'm the adjutant of the sovereign, Count Bolmashov.

531
00:52:06,898 --> 00:52:10,854
See you soon, my brave hero. From now on, I'm forever in your debt.

532
00:52:11,379 --> 00:52:13,402
But I am not accustomed to be long in debt.

533
00:52:19,481 --> 00:52:22,268
- What's your name? - It's Count, it doesn't matter!

534
00:52:31,241 --> 00:52:33,586
- Is Bolmashov still asleep? - He's snoring all over the place.

535
00:52:33,762 --> 00:52:35,716
He must be dreaming sweet dreams when he's frightened.

536
00:52:38,270 --> 00:52:41,228
Ah, Count. - Has the Field Marshal arrived? - We're waiting.

537
00:52:44,622 --> 00:52:46,261
Oh, the cornet at last. What about Zharovsky?

538
00:52:46,509 --> 00:52:48,835
- He sent a package to the Field Marshal. - Is he tired?

539
00:52:49,060 --> 00:52:53,282
- No. Just a little. Wash your face... You can rest from the road.

540
00:53:06,051 --> 00:53:08,084
How long has this valiant cornet been with you?

541
00:53:08,503 --> 00:53:10,353
Since the beginning of summer. His name is Azarov,

542
00:53:10,377 --> 00:53:12,615
He's a fine-looking boy. Only seventeen years old.

543
00:53:12,862 --> 00:53:16,443
But he's a good match for some of the old soldiers. What do you see in him?

544
00:53:16,704 --> 00:53:20,409
I have a suspicion I've met him.

545
00:53:20,604 --> 00:53:22,660
- So what of it? - Nothing, of course.

546
00:53:23,482 --> 00:53:26,946
Only I was less prepared to see him here.

547
00:54:05,288 --> 00:54:11,784
I'm pretty tired from that walk. I'll sigh before the parade.

548
00:54:12,373 --> 00:54:16,149
Give these buns to the prisoners.

549
00:54:20,444 --> 00:54:24,048
I wish this chair were closer to the stove.

550
00:54:26,392 --> 00:54:29,774
And a lower curtain, like this.

551
00:54:31,838 --> 00:54:35,249
I've heard that General Bolmashov is here.

552
00:54:38,081 --> 00:54:41,320
I know of his adventure.

553
00:54:44,000 --> 00:54:48,672
Well, I have no more errands to run. Go, all of you.

554
00:55:00,432 --> 00:55:02,246
/ Snore

555
00:55:02,852 --> 00:55:03,629
Ahem.

556
00:55:06,605 --> 00:55:10,082
- What's that for you, young man? - A package from Count Zharovsky to you personally!

557
00:55:10,127 --> 00:55:12,799
- Come on. What's your name? - Azarov.

558
00:55:13,381 --> 00:55:17,739
Well, that's good. Is Azarov Staff-Major your father?

559
00:55:17,913 --> 00:55:19,041
No, my uncle.

560
00:55:19,473 --> 00:55:24,331
He and I fought together at Ishmael against

561
00:55:24,355 --> 00:55:28,460
against the Turks. Yes. That was years ago.

562
00:55:29,471 --> 00:55:35,255
But our opponent is more famous. Bonaparte himself. How was it? Am I all right?

563
00:55:35,418 --> 00:55:36,745
Very well, Your Grace.

564
00:55:38,310 --> 00:55:43,504
It is. I think it's fine. Your first year in the service?

565
00:55:43,678 --> 00:55:45,248
Your Grace, my first.

566
00:55:45,963 --> 00:55:50,168
And all at headquarters? It must be boring, isn't it?

567
00:55:50,745 --> 00:55:53,547
I couldn't have lasted a week at your age.

568
00:55:53,754 --> 00:55:56,726
- I dare say... - Just give it up.

569
00:55:57,549 --> 00:56:01,273
You can't get your hands dirty in ink. Smell the gunpowder! Yes.

570
00:56:01,511 --> 00:56:03,417
- You've guessed my dream. - That's right.

571
00:56:05,955 --> 00:56:11,064
- Do you want me to leave? - Wait while I read it.

572
00:56:22,065 --> 00:56:27,549
Prince, when I hear that you are here, I want to lay down at your feet.

573
00:56:27,849 --> 00:56:31,080
- HQ? - I am here in the militia.

574
00:56:31,594 --> 00:56:36,695
Our nobility is Svarecki of Alov province, representative of Nurin Count.

575
00:56:39,100 --> 00:56:43,700
I have a question for you, a secret one, so to speak.

576
00:56:44,275 --> 00:56:45,882
Well, what's the secret?

577
00:56:46,533 --> 00:56:50,091
Go away for a minute, cornet, if the count asks it.

578
00:57:05,137 --> 00:57:07,257
Check it out for yourself, Prince.

579
00:57:07,527 --> 00:57:11,993
And I'll vouch for you. All hussars have moustaches, but this cornet...

580
00:57:12,231 --> 00:57:15,583
I'll ask him myself. But in the meantime, don't say a word about the staff.

581
00:57:15,791 --> 00:57:18,114
I swear to you, Prince. I'll be as hot as an oven.

582
00:57:18,322 --> 00:57:19,387
Send him to me.

583
00:57:38,124 --> 00:57:41,616
- You called, Your Grace? - Yes, Cornet.

584
00:57:45,843 --> 00:57:50,533
- Tell me, how old are you? - Seventeen.

585
00:57:54,288 --> 00:57:58,697
Aren't you afraid to fight in the war? Tell me without lying.

586
00:57:59,292 --> 00:58:01,988
- Oh, Your Grace, no! - I cannot lie.

587
00:58:02,012 --> 00:58:03,370
I dare not lie!

588
00:58:06,297 --> 00:58:10,528
And if you dare not lie, then tell me...

589
00:58:13,527 --> 00:58:14,822
No, wait.

590
00:58:17,381 --> 00:58:21,591
- What is your name, by the way? - According to my uncle, my name is Alexander.

591
00:58:22,305 --> 00:58:25,143
Right. Alexander? When you were a kid, was it Sashka?

592
00:58:25,349 --> 00:58:26,910
No. Shurka, Your Grace.

593
00:58:30,275 --> 00:58:35,889
Verkhalyov was in this room just now. Don't you know him? He's yours, from Smolensk.

594
00:58:36,012 --> 00:58:36,547
No!

595
00:58:39,534 --> 00:58:44,164
Hasn't he been to your uncle's house before? On occasions?

596
00:58:48,438 --> 00:58:54,263
Go on. No, wait! One more question.

597
00:58:54,969 --> 00:59:00,846
Don't be surprised if... Well, cornet, are you a woman?!

598
00:59:02,375 --> 00:59:06,448
I can't lie to you, Your Grace. I am a woman.

599
00:59:07,257 --> 00:59:14,292
What? How dare you? To make a comedy out of military honor?

600
00:59:14,923 --> 00:59:18,419
I wanted to be a hero. If my country's in trouble, I have no strength to be at home.

601
00:59:18,443 --> 00:59:22,919
No, Mother, you can't fool me! To make a woman a soldier!

602
00:59:23,664 --> 00:59:25,832
Without such help, we'd have broken Bonaparte's legs!

603
00:59:26,207 --> 00:59:31,506
And we'll drive him out of Russia without women! What trick did you use to get into the headquarters?

604
00:59:31,614 --> 00:59:35,526
I have a cousin. He was with us in winter. He left his uniform...

605
00:59:35,745 --> 00:59:40,372
Home! To madams, nannies, rags, dolls, dances!

606
00:59:40,714 --> 00:59:47,550
Yes. You'll have to get out of here at once! Your uncle doesn't know, does he? Are your parents alive?

607
00:59:47,824 --> 00:59:48,903
I've been an orphan since childhood.

608
00:59:49,278 --> 00:59:56,699
Right. Well, how could you do this deception? A uniform without the right to take it.

609
00:59:57,003 --> 00:59:58,414
May I say, Your Grace?

610
00:59:58,640 --> 01:00:03,028
No, I will not! I won't listen to a maiden's babble. Yes.

611
01:00:03,298 --> 01:00:07,233
The nonsense of the staff already makes my ears grow dull

612
01:00:07,257 --> 01:00:10,626
of the staff's nonsense enough as it is. Yes. I should feel pity for them at my age.

613
01:00:10,982 --> 01:00:15,346
And if the eyes are sharp, the hands are faithful in their sights, and the stirrups are not weak?

614
01:00:15,438 --> 01:00:19,182
And if all - mind, heart, strength, nerves - ask for orders?

615
01:00:19,716 --> 01:00:23,363
For thee, country, mother country, to give all for thee. And if...

616
01:00:23,570 --> 01:00:29,828
I beg you, speak briefly. I am old, mademoiselle. I'm tired of speeches.

617
01:00:30,951 --> 01:00:33,075
And besides, I don't take lectures from young ladies.

618
01:00:33,917 --> 01:00:36,989
Off you go. I tell you, the ball is over. Go now.

619
01:00:37,618 --> 01:00:39,914
- Let me stay. - There's nothing to think of.

620
01:00:41,488 --> 01:00:45,876
Well, I beg you, Prince... Well, Your Grace...

621
01:00:47,047 --> 01:00:53,614
I'm on my knees now! I beg you... I, I...

622
01:00:57,858 --> 01:01:00,376
Here come the tears in two streams.

623
01:01:02,695 --> 01:01:08,683
If anyone comes in... What do you want them to know about you? Я... I don't want to.

624
01:01:08,875 --> 01:01:16,187
Stay here in the hall until the tears are gone. Stop...

625
01:01:19,411 --> 01:01:28,129
I want to ask you something else. Did you go to the army, of course, to get a lover?

626
01:01:28,837 --> 01:01:32,130
I don't believe in sinlessness. I've sinned myself.

627
01:01:33,113 --> 01:01:36,877
- What? - My tears are dry all of a sudden.

628
01:01:37,029 --> 01:01:45,787
Have I offended you? Well, pardon the old man, my friend. But I'm going home tonight. That's not the point.

629
01:01:47,600 --> 01:01:49,318
No report for you, Your Grace.

630
01:01:49,775 --> 01:01:52,539
- Sit down, General. - From the Emperor.

631
01:01:57,972 --> 01:02:00,109
Did you hear the scandal that happened to me?

632
01:02:02,040 --> 01:02:09,212
Yes, it's not good. With a letter like that... Why didn't you have an escort?

633
01:02:09,747 --> 01:02:13,581
I had an escort, but not a big one, alas. If it hadn't been for that young cornet.

634
01:02:15,000 --> 01:02:17,997
The prince, imagine, no. He rode off without telling me his name.

635
01:02:18,235 --> 01:02:20,616
He was in a hurry with his errand. He's just a boy.

636
01:02:20,918 --> 01:02:24,564
That's the kind of boy who makes heroes out of his fatherland.

637
01:02:25,785 --> 01:02:31,937
Yes, Russia. In my mind, the Cross should be awarded to him for this deed.

638
01:02:35,018 --> 01:02:39,225
Are you still here? Go, and be gone by evening.

639
01:02:39,292 --> 01:02:43,213
My respects to your uncle. I'll write to him.

640
01:02:45,702 --> 01:02:49,782
Forgive me, for God's sake. I did not recognise you, my brave friend.

641
01:02:49,964 --> 01:02:51,789
But why are your eyes red?

642
01:02:52,725 --> 01:02:56,806
I guess there's a storm coming over you, my humble hero.

643
01:02:57,572 --> 01:03:02,155
By the way, Your Grace, I remember you wished to give him a cross for his deed just now.

644
01:03:02,783 --> 01:03:08,370
The prince must not retreat. He hath redeemed the provinces by his deed.

645
01:03:08,947 --> 01:03:12,428
And by the article should be awarded the Cross of St. George and the bow.

646
01:03:14,615 --> 01:03:20,918
Without him, I'd never be alive. Well, Prince! Don't you appreciate at all...

647
01:03:21,181 --> 01:03:25,698
...the life of an imperial adjutant? You're welcome to it.

648
01:03:34,714 --> 01:03:43,976
You've earned the cross by right for your exploits. Well, wear it with glory.

649
01:03:45,756 --> 01:03:47,646
I congratulate you.

650
01:03:49,664 --> 01:03:53,181
Let me go. I'll stay at headquarters until the parade.

651
01:03:55,783 --> 01:03:57,354
We shall meet again.

652
01:04:07,992 --> 01:04:12,056
I want no reward other than the right to fight in the war for my country.

653
01:04:12,791 --> 01:04:16,082
- Let me ask you for this award. - If you've earned it, wear it!

654
01:04:19,540 --> 01:04:28,935
That's no way to throw crosses. It's not a hairpin. Say thank you to the general.

655
01:04:29,678 --> 01:04:32,884
- May I stay? - And if anyone finds out?

656
01:04:33,115 --> 01:04:37,569
Like this count, that you... Well, not a man?

657
01:04:38,531 --> 01:04:42,942
I've been here six months. No one in that time has suspected neither face nor rank.

658
01:04:43,864 --> 01:04:47,062
And you will tell the count that he was deceived.

659
01:04:48,266 --> 01:04:55,303
Yes. They've been round me on every side. Well... Serve.

660
01:04:56,740 --> 01:05:01,618
The rank that you have worn so illicitly, it shall be yours.

661
01:05:02,453 --> 01:05:07,662
But don't throw it like a cross. It's not a comb. Off you go, then.

662
01:05:08,190 --> 01:05:12,068
- Thank you, Your Grace. - I'll keep my secret.

663
01:05:12,612 --> 01:05:16,109
I swear I'll keep my military honor! I'll justify your trust.

664
01:05:16,296 --> 01:05:18,995
I do. I do! Go.

665
01:05:26,353 --> 01:05:29,141
- Well? - There's a count at the door.

666
01:05:30,793 --> 01:05:32,279
Well, stay here.

667
01:05:34,747 --> 01:05:38,575
Count! Your anecdote, as I thought it would be, is nonsense.

668
01:05:38,599 --> 01:05:42,237
You should joke so low with an adjutant, not with me.

669
01:05:42,440 --> 01:05:46,581
My God, what a passage. I swear it, Your Grace.

670
01:05:46,775 --> 01:05:49,797
All right, all right. But don't joke so much again.

671
01:05:49,883 --> 01:05:51,432
Gee...

672
01:05:53,052 --> 01:06:02,274
Oh, it's you, Davyd. Well, brag. I love your lies. Who's that with you?

673
01:06:02,532 --> 01:06:05,870
- Lieutenant Rzhevsky! - You look like a hero.

674
01:06:06,055 --> 01:06:07,343
He'll be the first to fight.

675
01:06:07,572 --> 01:06:12,404
I've heard about your desperation. A hero, a hero.

676
01:06:12,652 --> 01:06:17,198
- I am flattered by your trust. - You've lived up to it more than once in battle.

677
01:06:19,154 --> 01:06:26,954
Aye. Well done! You would have been a prettier wench.

678
01:06:30,823 --> 01:06:34,746
- Oh, is that you? - Yes, it's me. Bonjour, Lieutenant.

679
01:06:34,842 --> 01:06:36,332
All the staff business?

680
01:06:36,603 --> 01:06:42,379
Business, don't get any better. How was your affair with Mademoiselle Germont?

681
01:06:42,556 --> 01:06:46,601
Haven't you heard? The squad was surrounded. Her enemies took her back the same night.

682
01:06:46,818 --> 01:06:49,231
Oh, my God, and you ran away?

683
01:06:49,309 --> 01:06:55,193
Three thousand! We'll duel again when we first meet.

684
01:06:55,429 --> 01:07:00,081
Well. You will not have long to wait. I'm joining your troop from headquarters.

685
01:07:10,993 --> 01:07:17,922
I have a riddle to solve. I give you my word that I will keep the secret. Are you or aren't you?

686
01:07:18,225 --> 01:07:24,333
Am I or am I not? But this is new. I am me.

687
01:07:25,259 --> 01:07:32,221
I'm in a hurry now, alas, I have no time for chatter. Goodbye, dear Count!

688
01:07:32,953 --> 01:07:36,108
But still, am I right or am I wrong?

689
01:07:52,820 --> 01:07:56,167
I have taken a prisoner. Of manners, I judge an officer.

690
01:07:56,597 --> 01:07:57,850
Tell me your rank.

691
01:07:58,035 --> 01:08:02,888
Lieutenant. Let me give it back to you From my heart I thank you, forever your friend.

692
01:08:02,965 --> 01:08:04,606
What is the meaning of this oath all of a sudden?

693
01:08:04,810 --> 01:08:06,685
I gave him my coat to keep him warm.

694
01:08:06,771 --> 01:08:08,754
- Are you French? - No, I am a Spaniard.

695
01:08:09,027 --> 01:08:13,243
He is no coward. The cold made him shoot wrong. His hand was shaking.

696
01:08:13,554 --> 01:08:18,592
This is the first time I've met such an enemy. I am glad now that I have not killed you in battle.

697
01:08:18,808 --> 01:08:21,929
Tell me your part. Well, answer me.

698
01:08:22,104 --> 01:08:23,549
I will not answer that question.

699
01:08:23,924 --> 01:08:25,811
Hmm. The song of the French is sung.

700
01:08:26,004 --> 01:08:29,097
Why must you keep your oath of allegiance?

701
01:08:29,367 --> 01:08:32,879
Or, sir, do I not hear you well? Or do you advise me to betray?

702
01:08:33,826 --> 01:08:36,436
What's in this war for you? For you are not a Frenchman.

703
01:08:36,636 --> 01:08:39,833
I could have betrayed them in their glory. But now you have won.

704
01:08:40,113 --> 01:08:42,660
It is my custom to be faithful to them.

705
01:08:54,659 --> 01:08:57,055
By the way, I have a plan for a sortie.

706
01:08:57,401 --> 01:09:01,012
Huh. A plan right off the bat? I can tell you're a staffer.

707
01:09:02,343 --> 01:09:07,155
Well, I'm kidding. Don't be too harsh. We'll talk.

708
01:09:09,866 --> 01:09:12,325
Our little town is on the road...

709
01:09:58,998 --> 01:10:01,923
My lieutenant, this one goes straight to headquarters Through the posts without telling the password.

710
01:10:02,128 --> 01:10:04,914
- We'll find out, go. - A blizzard is raging in the field.

711
01:10:05,155 --> 01:10:09,366
- I've been walking for a long time. I'm tired and so cold. - What do you want here?

712
01:10:09,391 --> 01:10:11,912
- The uniform of the Navarre riflemen. - Are you an officer?

713
01:10:12,298 --> 01:10:15,839
I was a prisoner. I escaped. I'll put my hand on my heart...

714
01:10:16,078 --> 01:10:18,328
...no one has ever endured such infernal suffering.

715
01:10:18,352 --> 01:10:20,213
Only I would know where my part is.

716
01:10:20,611 --> 01:10:22,646
Yes, in war, my friend, as in war.

717
01:10:22,958 --> 01:10:28,146
Navarre riflemen. Go to the other world, if you look for them. Alas, they are gone.

718
01:10:28,393 --> 01:10:30,808
- They can't be! - Come closer to the fire.

719
01:10:34,764 --> 01:10:40,824
Linier. Corneille. Printed in Paris.

720
01:10:41,084 --> 01:10:42,682
I didn't know paper burned like that.

721
01:10:42,869 --> 01:10:46,329
- What's your name? - Vincenzo Salgari.

722
01:10:59,988 --> 01:11:02,167
I'll find a corner so as not to disturb you here.

723
01:11:02,379 --> 01:11:06,958
No, Lieutenant, please wait here with us, the General should be back soon.

724
01:11:07,312 --> 01:11:12,330
He'll want to see you, he'll have plenty of questions. He's very curious, our Dewey.

725
01:11:12,759 --> 01:11:14,630
I'll answer them all with pleasure.

726
01:11:17,818 --> 01:11:21,513
My lieutenant, another fugitive, come in. He swears he's a French officer.

727
01:11:21,744 --> 01:11:26,271
And showed quite a lot of haste, As we called out. Barely got out of harm's way.

728
01:11:27,429 --> 01:11:32,872
I was a prisoner of war. My regiment was broken long ago. With whom to retreat now, I care not.

729
01:11:33,448 --> 01:11:36,644
But where is your uniform and other regalia? Your rank?

730
01:11:37,348 --> 01:11:42,608
I'm a lieutenant. They took my uniform in captivity. My name is Vincento Salgari.

731
01:11:46,565 --> 01:11:50,276
Wait a minute, damn it, I'm seeing double.

732
01:11:50,544 --> 01:11:54,952
It's not... I ask you to repeat your name.

733
01:11:55,219 --> 01:11:58,566
- Vincento Salgari. - And you, my dear knight?

734
01:11:58,909 --> 01:12:00,714
I'm a lieutenant in Murat's corps.

735
01:12:16,645 --> 01:12:20,150
Are you silent? That's great.

736
01:12:21,257 --> 01:12:26,136
Truly, I didn't recognize my brother! He's changed so much, you're alive, Vincento!

737
01:12:26,183 --> 01:12:28,870
- You're both Vincento? - Damn it.

738
01:12:29,129 --> 01:12:32,046
From birth to the grave it's our ancient ancestral law

739
01:12:32,070 --> 01:12:35,073
that all men are called Vincento in the family.

740
01:12:35,485 --> 01:12:38,747
Yes, I confess I haven't seen a moment like this in a long time.

741
01:12:39,197 --> 01:12:42,491
- I thought one of you was a spy. - Yes, but which one, me or him?

742
01:12:42,761 --> 01:12:44,794
Come sit by the fire, you're cold, aren't you?

743
01:12:45,020 --> 01:12:47,094
Yes, from my socks to my head.

744
01:13:11,028 --> 01:13:13,876
Thank you. I had no right to expect this from you.

745
01:13:14,110 --> 01:13:18,803
Allow me to congratulate you. You ran apart, but you met in our place.

746
01:13:20,283 --> 01:13:23,633
What a romance. But the fire is almost out.

747
01:13:23,794 --> 01:13:33,093
What are you burning? Oh, Barney, Rassin.

748
01:13:38,503 --> 01:13:41,226
The disposition of the main Russian forces, I wonder.

749
01:13:41,730 --> 01:13:44,161
What can you tell me? Well, you first.

750
01:13:44,730 --> 01:13:47,041
Ready, my general, to tell me all I know.

751
01:13:47,701 --> 01:13:51,849
No, sit down. You're tired. Well, I'm tired too.

752
01:13:53,963 --> 01:13:56,529
- Where do I start? - Don't say a word, my friend.

753
01:13:56,755 --> 01:13:59,690
- Die, but keep your mouth shut. - What's that supposed to mean?

754
01:13:59,735 --> 01:14:03,681
The ravings of a sick man! Why did you leave your bed? Go upstairs.

755
01:14:08,538 --> 01:14:13,392
No, wait. Which one do you know? Tell me.

756
01:14:13,545 --> 01:14:16,173
You, my angel, do not fear their threats.

757
01:14:16,537 --> 01:14:19,937
Don't answer their questions. For you are a maiden, not a soldier.

758
01:14:20,664 --> 01:14:25,956
Are you a woman?! How could you dare?

759
01:14:26,060 --> 01:14:29,778
She is my niece. I give you my word. She's seventeen years old.

760
01:14:30,019 --> 01:14:32,639
- That's new. - There's a whole family of spies.

761
01:14:32,896 --> 01:14:36,142
Who's the other one? Is he your nephew too? Or who?

762
01:14:36,218 --> 01:14:37,091
Oh, dear...

763
01:14:37,280 --> 01:14:39,354
I don't know who he is. This is the first time I have seen him.

764
01:14:39,684 --> 01:14:43,580
Did you not lend her your uniform, that you betrayed your oath?

765
01:14:43,815 --> 01:14:46,512
I swear I took it without asking! He did not know.

766
01:14:47,239 --> 01:14:55,966
No more questions. Yea, it is clear to me. Take him out. And shoot these men in the morning.

767
01:15:36,822 --> 01:15:40,797
Davyd! The cornet was captured! I barely escaped the pursuit.

768
01:15:41,558 --> 01:15:48,320
Now there's no need to wait for help! Alert! All hands on horseback!

769
01:16:39,676 --> 01:16:41,526
Three thousand devils!

770
01:16:44,309 --> 01:16:46,308
You saved me, I am eternally grateful!

771
01:16:46,544 --> 01:16:50,657
- Madam, I never expected to meet you. - I'm still so happy to meet you.

772
01:16:50,862 --> 01:16:52,599
But your cousin, is he still alive now?

773
01:16:52,922 --> 01:16:58,055
Of course he is! He's locked up there in the closet. I'll get him. No, wait here.

774
01:16:58,706 --> 01:17:05,318
I'm soaked from all this riding. Three thousand devils, a date like in a novel.

775
01:17:19,570 --> 01:17:23,749
- Lieutenant, I am your slave. - I'll settle up with you. Who's that dandy?

776
01:17:23,932 --> 01:17:25,672
Our friend, though a French lieutenant.

777
01:19:54,760 --> 01:19:57,154
You bastards! They started shooting again.

778
01:19:58,040 --> 01:19:59,029
It's dawn.

779
01:19:59,423 --> 01:20:02,573
The general wanted to shoot us at dawn.

780
01:20:06,036 --> 01:20:14,096
He keeps his word... At least as far as I'm concerned.

781
01:20:21,879 --> 01:20:25,322
There's still fighting. Do you hear that thunder? Let's go, Cornet.

782
01:20:25,560 --> 01:20:28,111
We can't leave the house. Orders and maps are here.

783
01:20:28,635 --> 01:20:31,010
It's good booty. Let them know our partisan

784
01:20:31,034 --> 01:20:33,589
It is the custom of our partisans to beat the enemies of the fatherland until they have surrendered.

785
01:20:34,206 --> 01:20:37,501
I know not how to thank you. You saved me,

786
01:20:37,525 --> 01:20:40,712
my uncle and my cousin. She's probably out of her senses now.

787
01:20:41,119 --> 01:20:41,852
It's nothing, brother.

788
01:20:44,685 --> 01:20:47,308
Besides, I'll bet she imagined, of course...

789
01:20:47,568 --> 01:20:50,820
...that you came here so brazenly for her.

790
01:20:51,247 --> 01:20:55,869
Don't talk nonsense. Why don't you load your gun? The fight's not over yet.

791
01:20:57,342 --> 01:21:01,756
Do you remember, Lieutenant, the wager? If you save the girl...

792
01:21:02,014 --> 01:21:06,126
...you will marry her. We shall soon be feasting at the wedding?

793
01:21:06,437 --> 01:21:10,433
That's no good! I wanted to save you, but I don't care about her.

794
01:21:11,810 --> 01:21:17,427
The whole troop witnessed the bet. You shouldn't refuse. I'm awfully glad...

795
01:21:17,717 --> 01:21:21,086
...to congratulate you on your enviable lot in life. So you're getting married?

796
01:21:21,366 --> 01:21:25,042
I don't want to hear any more of your nonsense. I've lost the wager, but know this...

797
01:21:25,269 --> 01:21:28,129
...you will not feast at your wedding! We'll continue the duel.

798
01:21:28,566 --> 01:21:32,396
But, indeed, the occasion is small. And too uncomfortable here at the manor.

799
01:21:32,603 --> 01:21:35,478
If thou art not a coward, I pray thee, come to the barrier!

800
01:21:35,927 --> 01:21:42,040
Save me, and kill me again? Well, that's right, it's too hussar-like. Shall we postpone it?

801
01:21:42,436 --> 01:21:45,442
You're a coward, you punk! Boy!

802
01:21:54,428 --> 01:22:01,815
Shoot on the count of three! I'm counting! One, two...

803
01:22:02,453 --> 01:22:04,218
Stop, gentlemen!

804
01:22:05,826 --> 01:22:08,138
- I made it. - Three thousand devils!

805
01:22:08,261 --> 01:22:09,790
Haven't you had enough deaths in the war?!

806
01:22:09,994 --> 01:22:13,018
Where do you come from, Germont? Be a witness, as to this dandy...

807
01:22:13,223 --> 01:22:16,468
I'll put a bullet in his forehead! Cornet, to the barrier!

808
01:22:16,757 --> 01:22:20,881
My God, who are these people? Don't you dare, gentlemen. I don't want it at all.

809
01:22:21,038 --> 01:22:25,418
I'll make it up to you, just a word. You want to fight over me?

810
01:22:25,966 --> 01:22:29,920
Then know that I love the other. I do not care for either of you.

811
01:22:30,093 --> 01:22:30,778
Alas!

812
01:22:31,017 --> 01:22:35,162
Mademoiselle Germain, what's that got to do with us? You may love the devil. Be my guest.

813
01:22:35,708 --> 01:22:39,694
I am insulted by the cornet. Only by blood can I wash away this insult.

814
01:22:50,519 --> 01:22:56,588
Mademoiselle Germont? That's strange. We're lucky to meet her now.

815
01:22:56,931 --> 01:22:59,021
- The arm, what's wrong with it? - Ah, an empty wound.

816
01:22:59,496 --> 01:23:02,486
Pierre, my friend. For you, believe me, I long.

817
01:23:02,510 --> 01:23:04,143
It's hard to believe it.

818
01:23:04,514 --> 01:23:08,629
Pierre, don't say that. I'm terribly glad. I believe happiness is given to us...

819
01:23:08,813 --> 01:23:12,292
- Mademoiselle Germont! - Louise. Call me as you used to call me.

820
01:23:12,522 --> 01:23:16,965
Kiss me as you kissed me before We quarreled at my whim

821
01:23:17,234 --> 01:23:22,457
- I blame myself. - Louisa. Louisa, I'm an ass.

822
01:23:41,199 --> 01:23:44,346
- Again, Germont! Brother, however, - Where is the cornet?

823
01:23:44,841 --> 01:23:46,786
He and the Lieutenant went there to shoot.

824
01:23:46,978 --> 01:23:47,822
Oh, shit!

825
01:23:55,448 --> 01:23:57,395
No, you can't do without a crowbar here.

826
01:23:57,569 --> 01:24:01,837
I am Azarov. I'm the owner of this house. Retired staff-major.

827
01:24:02,479 --> 01:24:06,816
- And your eternally obedient subject. - Cornet Azarov is your nephew?

828
01:24:07,027 --> 01:24:09,291
- Niece. - What do you mean?

829
01:24:09,440 --> 01:24:12,518
- What is this nonsense? - I think he's delirious. - I see.

830
01:24:12,861 --> 01:24:17,340
You doubt it for nothing. Ivan can tell you. He's been babysitting her since she was a baby.

831
01:24:17,534 --> 01:24:18,857
A maiden, that's right.

832
01:24:19,051 --> 01:24:22,290
What an affair! And I thought the old man was a child!

833
01:24:22,314 --> 01:24:24,765
- Ah, ah, ah! /Shots fired/

834
01:24:25,053 --> 01:24:27,220
- God have mercy. - Break down the door!

835
01:24:38,267 --> 01:24:40,534
- Killed?! - Wounded? - Oh, my God!

836
01:24:42,995 --> 01:24:46,432
- You will answer me now. - There's the duelist, too.

837
01:24:46,662 --> 01:24:51,363
He saw a mouse and fell unconscious. That's the kind of ending that makes me want to shoot.

838
01:24:51,547 --> 01:24:52,105
You did shoot, didn't you?

839
01:24:52,310 --> 01:24:56,583
Yes. In a mouse hunt, I killed a few, missed one. That's a shame.

840
01:24:57,841 --> 01:25:00,134
Please, you've got to slow down.

841
01:25:00,310 --> 01:25:03,742
She's always been afraid of mice, ever since she was a baby.

842
01:25:03,999 --> 01:25:07,224
- She?! Allow me, sir. I must...

843
01:25:07,408 --> 01:25:09,954
You must? Oh, damn, am I dreaming?

844
01:25:10,193 --> 01:25:13,442
I must ask your forgiveness, all of you, for my deceit.

845
01:25:15,085 --> 01:25:19,651
- She's a maiden! - My friend, it's a sin to judge success.

846
01:25:21,642 --> 01:25:24,153
I must present you, for your valor, to the rank of Lieutenant.

847
01:25:24,177 --> 01:25:26,004
to the rank of lieutenant.

848
01:25:26,414 --> 01:25:28,383
- You are too kind. - But how...

849
01:25:28,558 --> 01:25:29,939
Better be silent, brother.

850
01:25:33,441 --> 01:25:36,731
I pray you, gentlemen, champagne. In honour of deliverance.

851
01:25:37,043 --> 01:25:40,478
- What doubt can there be? - You're right, my friend! Come, come!

852
01:26:10,678 --> 01:26:16,315
Lieutenant, wait, where are you going? You and I still have some explaining to do, don't we?

853
01:26:17,399 --> 01:26:21,846
Do you agree with me? How long your astonishment lasts.

854
01:26:22,381 --> 01:26:30,403
Yes, I am not a man. Alas, alas, alas. Are you sorry, too? For you are my teacher...

855
01:26:30,641 --> 01:26:41,270
...in hussar's prowess. Well, why are you silent? Tell me, do you love me?

856
01:26:41,785 --> 01:26:45,164
He that is in sound mind will not live a day who is in love with you.

857
01:26:45,509 --> 01:26:47,951
No, speak plainly, are you in love with me?

858
01:26:48,126 --> 01:26:50,835
He who loves you, yes, would jump out of his mind.

859
01:26:51,222 --> 01:26:53,203
I'm as stubborn as you are. Yes or no?

860
01:26:53,550 --> 01:27:03,956
- I'd like to say goodbye to you forever. - Good. But still, do you love? Well?

861
01:27:04,295 --> 01:27:10,631
Yes. Three thousand devils. No, that doesn't sound like anything.

862
01:27:10,984 --> 01:27:13,827
That's the compote. No, better a hundred deaths. I'm

863
01:27:13,851 --> 01:27:16,393
I'm ashamed to look you in the eye, believe me.

864
01:27:16,759 --> 01:27:19,221
You are in love and beg for death, but why?

865
01:27:19,532 --> 01:27:23,725
You must despise me, I was an ass. Farewell.

866
01:27:23,964 --> 01:27:28,671
Wait. Once we were so friendly, remember, That we were so friendly?

867
01:27:29,528 --> 01:27:33,083
Knit your hands, what the devil am I saying? If

868
01:27:33,107 --> 01:27:36,990
I beg your pardon for that impertinence at the ball.

869
01:27:38,164 --> 01:27:47,184
You kissed me that night, too. I am indebted to you. Now I'll repay it.

870
01:27:51,903 --> 01:27:56,117
Well, you may go. What are you doing?

871
01:27:58,285 --> 01:28:03,951
I'll be right back. Do you remember the bet?

872
01:28:06,121 --> 01:28:08,524
- Well? - If I save the girl...

873
01:28:09,317 --> 01:28:14,186
You must marry her, don't you think? I'll spare you the bet.

874
01:28:14,685 --> 01:28:19,309
It was very unpleasant for you, you do not tolerate my cousin. I mean me.

875
01:28:19,843 --> 01:28:22,171
I swear to you now, I have never loved so!

876
01:28:23,412 --> 01:28:26,366
I'll seek death in battle if you will not agree to be mine.

877
01:28:27,800 --> 01:28:34,001
Farewell forever. I'm going, but if... Shit!

878
01:28:34,078 --> 01:28:39,361
My knight, wait! Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

879
01:28:48,135 --> 01:28:51,823
/ Singing a song / Life takes us a long way.

880
01:28:51,847 --> 01:28:55,401
To laugh, to cry or not to cry all the same.

881
01:28:55,844 --> 01:28:58,919
When the chorus is old and old and old

882
01:28:58,943 --> 01:29:03,302
Once upon a time, once upon a time, once upon a time.

883
01:29:03,817 --> 01:29:11,076
I used to fight all kinds of things! Bottles of many, very many have seen the bottom!

884
01:29:11,654 --> 01:29:14,924
But I've never been so in love.

885
01:29:14,948 --> 01:29:18,973
Long time ago, long time ago, long time ago!

886
01:29:20,063 --> 01:29:27,202
To the hero with the puffy moustache My heart, my heart was given forever.

887
01:29:27,958 --> 01:29:30,586
How long have we been enemies?

888
01:29:30,610 --> 01:29:35,031
Long ago, long ago, long ago, long ago!

889
01:29:35,872 --> 01:29:43,202
The years will pass, and from the distance Of years gone by, of years gone by One glimpses:

890
01:29:43,757 --> 01:29:46,291
How our grandfathers fought.

891
01:29:46,315 --> 01:29:51,112
Long time ago, long time ago, long time ago!

892
01:29:52,476 --> 01:29:55,984
And if the enemy, in the blind hope of conquering Russia.

893
01:29:56,008 --> 01:29:59,540
Will come to us again, will come to us again...

894
01:30:00,105 --> 01:30:08,821
We'll chase him, just like before - Long, long, long ago, long ago!

895
01:30:09,009 --> 01:30:13,870
